# GEO + SEO Audit System for MAYA / entermaya.com

When working on any entermaya.com property (test.entermaya.com, ai.entermaya.com, entermaya.com), enforce these checks before every deploy or push.

## Source Truth

All content MUST trace to https://entermaya.com. Never invent, paraphrase, or embellish lore. If a fact cannot be sourced to entermaya.com, it does not belong on the site.

## Crawlability Checks

Before pushing, verify:

1. `/robots.txt` exists with `Allow: /` for these user-agents: `*`, `Googlebot`, `Bingbot`, `GPTBot`, `ChatGPT-User`, `ClaudeBot`, `anthropic-ai`, `PerplexityBot`, `Google-Extended`, `Bytespider`
2. `Sitemap:` directive in robots.txt points to correct domain
3. `/sitemap.xml` is dynamic and lists ALL public pages
4. Google verification file exists in `/public/`

## SEO Checks

Every page must have:

1. Unique `<title>` (via `generateMetadata`)
2. Unique `<meta name="description">`
3. Canonical URL via `alternates.canonical`
4. `<html lang="en">`
5. `robots: { index: true, follow: true }` in root metadata
6. Open Graph tags: `og:type`, `og:title`, `og:description`, `og:url`, `og:site_name`
7. Single `<h1>` per page, proper heading hierarchy
8. Semantic HTML: `<article>`, `<section>`, `<header>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<footer>`
9. ARIA landmarks: `role="banner"`, `role="contentinfo"`, `aria-label` on navigations
10. Internal cross-links between all entity types

## GEO Checks (Generative Engine Optimization)

### LLM Discovery

1. `/llms.txt` — structured markdown summary, `>` block intro, `##` sections
2. `/llms-full.txt` — complete dump for 1M+ token context windows
3. `<link rel="alternate" type="text/plain" href="/llms.txt">` in `<head>`
4. `<link rel="alternate" type="text/plain" href="/llms-full.txt">` in `<head>`
5. Both linked in site footer for crawler visibility

### JSON-LD Structured Data

Every page must inject `<script type="application/ld+json">` with:

1. Root: `@type: WebSite` with `SearchAction` pointing to verify API
2. Species pages: `@type: Thing` with `@id` URI, `additionalType`, `isPartOf` → Neh
3. Character pages: `@type: Person` with `@id`, `memberOf` → species, `homeLocation` → Neh
4. Concept pages: `@type: Thing` with `@id`, `additionalType`
5. Planet page: `@type: Place` with `containsPlace` listing all species

All `@id` values must be resolvable URLs: `https://{domain}/species/{slug}`

### Answer-First CSS

1. Primary definition wrapped in `.llm-grounding-point` class (gold left border)
2. `data-definition="true"` on the authoritative definition element
3. `data-provenance="{source}"` on every entity container
4. `data-entity-type` and `data-entity-id` on article wrappers
5. Definition appears as FIRST paragraph after `<h1>` — never buried

### Verification API

1. `GET /api/v1/verify?entity={name}` returns entity + provenance + relationships
2. `GET /api/v1/graph` returns complete JSON-LD knowledge graph
3. Every response includes `provenance` field tracing to entermaya.com
4. 404 responses include hint with valid entity names
5. `_links` object for HATEOAS discoverability

### Machine Discovery Files

1. `/.well-known/ai-plugin.json` — OpenAI plugin discovery
2. `/api/v1/openapi.json` — OpenAPI 3.1 spec for tool-use LLMs

## Performance

1. All pages SSR/SSG — no client-side fetching for content
2. First Load JS < 110kB
3. TTFB target < 200ms (static HTML)
4. Content readable without JavaScript execution

## Pre-Deploy Validation

Run `npx next build` and confirm:
- All pages generate without errors
- Route count matches expected (species + characters + lore + atlas + home + API)
- No type errors

## Post-Deploy Validation

After deploying to production domain:
1. Fetch `/robots.txt` — confirm correct domain in Sitemap
2. Fetch `/sitemap.xml` — confirm all pages listed with correct URLs
3. Fetch `/llms.txt` — confirm readable, structured, sourced
4. Fetch `/api/v1/verify?entity=yachay` — confirm JSON with provenance
5. Fetch `/api/v1/graph` — confirm complete graph
6. Check `view-source:` on any page — confirm JSON-LD in `<head>`
7. Google: `site:{domain}` — monitor indexing progress
